Tama.
Van Ybiernas
· 2 hrs · Quezon City, Philippines ·
Sagot sa post ni TP:
Yun nga ang problema! Bina-bale-wala, tine-take for granted ng mga tao ang mga nandyan lang through thick and thin. Mas nakapocus sila doon... sa mga ---supposedly--- may ma-contribute sa kanila. Yung merong something to bring to the table, politically.
So, magugulat ka, magre-reach-out ang "nanalo" sa "natalo" kasi gusto nya makuha ang suporta ng mga natalo. Ina-assume nila na di naman mawawala ang suporta ng mga supporters, kasi nga supporters ang mga iyan. Loyal!
So, ang tinatarget nila ---ang binibiyayaan--- ay yung mga balimbing. Yung nasa kabila dati, pero lilipat ngayon kasi may mapapakinabangan. Iniisip kasi ng mga nanalo na may additional na maibibigay yung mga balimbing sa kanila: dagdag suporta, yung optics ng isang dating kaaway na kaibigan na ngayon, etc.
So, ang diskarte ng mga balimbing ay kumbinsihin ang mga nanalo na kailangan sila ng mga ito. At siyempre, may hihingin silang kapalit.
Eh yung mga supporters? Steady lang kayo. Kasi, supporters na kayo e. Hindi na kayo kailangan ligawan pa. Hindi na kayo kailangan suyuin pa. Yung mga balimbing ang mas kailangan suyuin at ligawan.
Bakit? Kasi yung mga balimbing at saka ang mga nanalo, nakatingin na sa future, sa 2019, 2022 at lampas pa.
Op kors, tama si TP na hindi kasama si PRRD dito kasi hindi naman nakatingin LAMPAS sa 2022 ang pangulo; nakapokus siya sa kasalukuyan hanggang 2022. Trabaho lang!
So, ang dumidiskarte rito ay yung mga buwitre na umiikot-ikot sa Malakanyang, nagpa-plano para sa future nila NA HINDI NA KASAMA SI DUTERTE. Kasi nga, wala naman plano si Duterte lampas sa 2022.
Tino-tolerate naman sila ng pangulo kasi hindi naman niya kaya kumilos mag-isa. Kailangan nya ng tulong.
Bilib na nga ako noong una na puro Tanders ang kinuha ng pangulo. Sa isip ko, "Ang galing!" Kumbaga sa kasaysayan ng Tsina, ang tawag sa mga tanders ay "eunuchs". Bakit? Kasi, walang future ang mga ito. Kinapon na ang future nila! Ang ambisyoso ay ang mga bata. Yan ang tumitingin sa future (na hindi na kasama si Duterte).
Yan, TP, ang mga buma-bale-wala, tume-take for granted sa MGA SUPPORTERS NI DUTERTE.
Sapagkat, nakatingin na sila sa future na wala si Duterte.
Yan ang mga taong puro hidden agenda ang nasa likod ng pagkilos nila. Kaya nga inimbento ng Tsina ang mga eunuchs. Kaya nga kailangan natin ang mga eunuchs. Hindi ang mga ambisyoso.
Eunuchs ang kailangan ng Pangulong Duterte...
Just a thought...

Who serves as a check-and-balance for Traditional Media?
Department of Transportation - Philippines
· 5 hrs ·
DOTr PRESS STATEMENT
09 November 2017
The Department of Transportation (DOTr) finds the ABS-CBN story titled "Tugade: Pray for MRT" misleading and malicious.
...
Issues concerning the MRT-3 are serious, and the DOTr is serious in solving them. We are taking bold steps to ensure that the system is safe and reliable. We are not just waiting for a miracle.
At the sidelines of the NLEX Harbor Link inspection today, DOTr Secretary Arthur Tugade told the media:
"TULUNGAN NIYO PO KAMI. BIGYAN NYO KAMI NG TIWALA. AMBUNAN NYO KAMI NG DASAL. 'PAGKAT ANG PROBLEMA HO SA MRT AY MASYADONG MALAWAK AT MALALIM. HUWAG TAYO UMASA NG MILAGRO PERO GAGAWIN NATIN ANG ATING MAKAKAYA."
While that exact quote was used by ABS-CBN in its story, it is clear, however, that the headline was meant to put malice into Secretary Tugade's statement. A clickbait, perhaps?
The DOTr urges ABS-CBN to be truthful, and not post misleading headlines, if it were to really serve the Filipino people.

So pag socmed policy, pwede pakialaman ng mainstream. Pero pag nag kwestyon ang socmed sa tinaguriang mainstream, ukol sa classification, hihiyaw na ng, "press freedom! regulation!" kulang nalang mag pa cry cry pa ng, "Inaapi kami!"
See Translation
Luminous by Trixie Cruz-Angeles
· Yesterday at 15:35 · Malabon City, Philippines ·
Remember when PCOO came up with a policy on blogger accreditation? Ang daming hanash! kesyo walang editors ang socmed, di gaya ng mainstream, na kesyo bakit gan...un lang ang requirements, na kesyo hindi naman sila news...
So pag socmed policy, pwede pakialaman ng mainstream. Pero pag nag kwestyon ang socmed sa tinaguriang mainstream, ukol sa classification, hihiyaw na ng, "press freedom! regulation!" kulang nalang mag pa cry cry pa ng, "Inaapi kami!" Narinig na namin yang pa-victim na yan, ha. Di na nga bumebenta eh.
At sus! Ang layo naman ng regulation sa reclassification. Paano naman ma repress ang press freedom pag reclassify ang Rappler, aber? Pipigilan ba sila mag blog? Magsulat? Magpublish? Magsalita? May mga pa-Facebook post pa nga kayo, napigilan ba kayo? Na report ba? Na take down ba?
Pero pag mainstream, pinipigilan ang pag accredit sa socmed kasi -- aminin na -- ayaw na andun ang bloggers sa press briefings.
Sa tutoo lang, ang gusto ng socmed, fair treatment. Yung bang equal lang. Kaso gusto ng kabila mas equal sila kaysa sa socmed.

SO I HAVE BROUGHT NOTHING BUT SHAME TO MY FAMILY
In 2000, someone who should be giving me unconditional love told me that I should live my life as a man and not... be myself. Otherwise, she said, nothing would happen in my life. Yup, she wanted me to follow her. She said that by living as a transgender woman, I'm bringing shame to the family. She rejected me. I almost killed myself.
In 2002, I co-founded the first transgender women's organization in the Philippines.
In 2009, I became the first Filipino to have her speech at the United Nation featured in its Official You Tube channel. Prior to that, I have already travelled a lot, being invited by different organizations, which includes the Swedish and French governments to talk about transgender issues.
In May 2012
- I won the Best Speaker Award in the 2012 The Hague European International Model United Nations
In July 2012
- I won the best delegate award in the 2012 Paris International Model United Nations
In 2013
- I became the first Filipino to have received the ECHO Award, given annually to excellent migrant students in academic and higher professional education in The Netherlands
In 2014
- I have received the Harry Benjamin Distinguished Education and Advocacy Award in recognition of valuable contributions to advocacy for transgender equality and rights
- I graduated magna cum laude at Leiden University College and also received received the Global Citizenship Award
In 2017
- I became the first transgender woman in the Philippines to have her own political column in a newspaper
- I finished my masters degree in International Relations, with a masters thesis given a very high grade
If the Liberal Party of the Philippines thinks that it could break my spirit by using the words of someone whose rejection fuelled me to make the best out of my life, YOU ARE MISTAKEN! You are messing with the wrong person Liberal Party. Wrong person.
I am just starting.
What you've demonstrated to Filipinos, Liberal Party of the Philippines, is that you are USERS. You've used the LGBT community during the elections. And now you are using someone who rejected her child because she's transgender in order to forward your political agenda to return to power. You are FAKE LIBERALS. One day I will expose to the world what you're doing right now. And I'll make you eat shit before an international audience. Watch me roar.
And Jover Laurio, Cocoy Dayao et al...I'll see you guys in court.

Rappler is panicking?
MOCHA USON BLOG
· 7 November at 13:16 ·
Sagutin po natin isa isa ang argumento ng Rappler
Sabi ng Rappler-- Rappler is an independent private media company. Because the Constitution guarantees freedom... of the press (Art. III, Section 4), government does not have the power to regulate independent media.
ANSWER (sagot ko): First of all to RECLASSIFY doesn’t mean to regulate. You still have the freedom to say what you want. No one is stopping you from publishing your blog. Maganda nga po itanong ay ayaw niyo ma regulate kayo pero ang mga bloggers gusto niyo i-regulate sa Malacanang? Di ba u even ask bakit hindi sa inyo nagkaroon ng consultation kahit meron naman nangyaring consultation. Ano ito one way lang na relationship?
2) Sabi ng Rappler--- The Malacañang Press Corps (MPC) is an independent group unattached to any government agency and is not under government control nor the supervision of the Presidential Communications Operations Office (PCOO).
ANSWER (sagot ko)- Yes hindi kayo nasa ilalim ng PCOO. Sino ba nagsabi na nasa ilalim kayo ng PCOO? RECLASSIFY lang ang request ko po. Paki google meaning ng RECLASSIFY
Sabi nv Rappler-- MPC by-laws are explicit on accreditation and cover online news organizations like Rappler. Section 2 under “Qualifications for MPC Membership” states: “For internet-based media, the reporter must represent a website affiliated with a duly-recognized print/radio/TV agency, or established online news organization with regular deployment of personnel in major beats.”
ANSWER (sagot ko): Pero teka... Ano definition ng “established news organization”? Maganda siguro itanong ay ito- why MPC is trying to regulate kung sino ang pwedeng pumasok na media sa Malacañang? Pero ayaw niyo ma REGULATE? one way nanaman?
3) Sabi ng Rappler-- The PCOO’s Interim Social Media Practitioner Accreditation covers only individuals and not news organizations. Section 5 of the PCOO’s Department Order 15 is categorical: “Social Media accreditation shall be issued to a Filipino Citizen who is at least eighteen (18) years of age, with not less than five thousand (5,000) followers in any social media platform.”
ANSWER (sagot ko)- So your argument is hindi naman kayo individual at kayo naman ay News Organization? Therefore ang MindaVote since News Organization sila, Mainstream Media na din sila? Hindi lang yan. Marami pang Blogger na News Organization at hindi individual so hindi sila classified as Social Media???
And btw Rappler, si Sec Martin ang tinatanong ko pero kayo ang sumasagot ng mabilis. Nagpapanic na ba kayo? Nagtatanong lang po.
